mount tsurugi (剱岳 tsurugi-dake) is located in the eastern area of toyama prefecture, japan. it is one of the tallest peak in the hida mountains at 2,999 m (9,839 ft). it is one of the 100 famous japanese mountains, and is called "the most dangerous mountain" climbable. tsurugi has a number of routes which approach world class long routes. it is recognised in japan as "the" premiere mountaineering peak in winter. although dangerous, its death toll is a small fraction of those who have died on japan's much smaller, but more lethal tanigawa-dake.